# 9.0 Docs

## Core .NET libraries

- [Ambiguous overload resolution affecting StringValues implicit operators](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/ambiguous-overload.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where ambiguous overload resolution now throws error CS0121.
- [API obsoletions with custom diagnostic IDs](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/obsolete-apis-with-custom-diagnostics.md): Learn about the APIs that have been marked as obsolete in .NET 9 with a custom diagnostic ID.
- [BigInteger maximum length](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/biginteger-limit.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where a maximum length for BigInteger is enforced.
- [BinaryReader.ReadString() returns "/uFFFD" on malformed sequences](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/binaryreader.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where BinaryReader.ReadString() returns "\uFFFD" on malformed encoded string sequences.
- [C# overload resolution prefers `params` span-type overloads](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/params-overloads.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 9 where C# overload resolution prefers `params` span-type overloads, which can't be used in `Expression` lambdas.
- [Creating type of array of System.Void not allowed](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/type-instance.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where it's no longer allowed to create a type of array of System.Void.
- [EnumConverter validates registered types to be enum](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/enumconverter.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change where EnumConverter now validates that the type to be registered is an enum type.
- [`Equals`/`GetHashCode` throw for `InlineArrayAttribute` types](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/inlinearrayattribute.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where the default implementations of `Equals()` and `GetHashCode()` throw an exception for types marked with `InlineArrayAttribute`.
- [FromKeyedServicesAttribute no longer injects non-keyed parameter](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/non-keyed-params.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries (dependency injection) where FromKeyedServicesAttribute no longer injects a non-keyed parameter.
- [IncrementingPollingCounter initial callback is asynchronous](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/async-callback.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where the IncrementingPollingCounter initial callback is no longer synchronous.
- [Inline array struct size limit is enforced](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/inlinearray-size.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where the size limit for inline arrays is now enforced.
- [InMemoryDirectoryInfo prepends rootDir to files](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/inmemorydirinfo-prepends-rootdir.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where InMemoryDirectoryInfo prepends the root directory to its file paths.
- [New TimeSpan.From*() overloads that take integers](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/timespan-from-overloads.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where new TimeSpan.From*() overloads were introduced that take integer arguments.
- [New version of some OOB packages](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/oob-packages.md): Learn about the breaking change in core .NET libraries where updates were made to TFMs and package versions for several OOB packages.
- [RuntimeHelpers.GetSubArray returns different type](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/getsubarray-return.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where the type of array instance returned by RuntimeHelpers.GetSubArray matches the source array.
- [String.Trim(params ReadOnlySpan<char>) overload removed](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/string-trim.md): Learn about the breaking change in core .NET libraries where the String.Trim*(params ReadOnlySpan<char>) methods have been removed due to potential behavioral changes.
- [Support for empty environment variables](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/empty-env-variable.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where passing `string.Empty` to `Environment.SetEnvironmentVariable` no longer deletes the environment variable.
- [ZipArchiveEntry names and comments respect UTF8 flag](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/main/docs/core/compatibility/core-libraries/9.0/ziparchiveentry-encoding.md): Learn about the .NET 9 breaking change in core .NET libraries where ZipArchiveEntry names and comments now respect the UTF8 flag when decoding.
